  "prompt": "Can people see if you have viewed their instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, whether people can see if you've viewed their content depends on the type of content:\n\n1. Stories:\n- People can see who has viewed their Instagram Stories\n- They can see a list of viewers\n- Viewers are listed in order of when they viewed the story\n\n2. Reels and Posts:\n- People cannot see who specifically viewed their regular posts or Reels\n- They can only see the total number of views/likes\n\n3. Close Friends Stories:\n- People can see who has viewed their Close Friends Stories\n- Only members of their Close Friends list can view these stories\n\n4. Live Videos:\n- During a live video, the person hosting can see who is watching\n- After the live video ends, they can see who viewed it\n\nSo, for most Instagram content (posts, Reels), you can browse anonymously. However, if you view someone's Story, they will be able to see that you have viewed it.",
